org.psygrid.data.model.hibernate.Narrati.name: Narrative 1
org.psygrid.data.model.hibernate.Narrati.displayText: ASK FOR AN EXAMPLE OF HOW EACH QUESTION ANWERED POSITIVELY. org.psygrid.data.model.hibernate.Narrati.name: Narrative 2
org.psygrid.data.model.hibernate.Narrati.displayText: DELUSIONS ARE 'BIZARRE' IF: CLEARLY IMPLAUSIBLE, ABSURD, NOT UNDERSTANDABLE, AND CANNOT DERIVE FROM ORDINARY LIFE EXPERIENCE.

org.psygrid.data.model.hibernate.Narrati.name: Narrative 3
org.psygrid.data.model.hibernate.Narrati.displayText: HALLUCINATIONS ARE SCORED 'BIZARRE' IF: A VOICE COMMENTS ON THE PERSON'S THOUGHTS OR BEHAVIOR, OR WHEN TWO OR MORE VOICES ARE CONVERSING WITH EACH OTHER.

org.psygrid.data.model.hibernate.Narrati.displayText: USE THE CLINICIAN JUDGEMENT OPTIONS ONLY IF THE CLINICIAN KNOWS FROM OTHER OUTSIDE EVIDENCE (FOR EXAMPLE, FAMILY INPUT) THAT THE SYMPTOM IS PRESENT BUT IS BEING DENIED BY THE PATIENT.
